language: Kadazan Dusun of Taginambur, Kota Belud, Sabah, Malaysia

annotation: 1. Whole thing; all; every nit of s.t.
2. Totally; absolutely; at all; all (the whole quantity of something)
(SA) < *se-ada-ña 'all there is, the lot of it'
All, everyone, whole. Archaic, used in church (Sph)
only used as bound form with pronouns e.g. amusimu = all of us
The distinction between those two lexical items is not clear
Serial verb meaning 'complete' that inflects to agree with the subject, used for universal quantification
WP: ngàra kua L, VL: ngara kua
